findings.reasoning: The finding claims that withdrawals will revert if the Team address is not set. While it is true that safeTransferFrom to address(0) reverts, the Team address is an uninitialized state variable that the owner is expected to set. More importantly, this is not the target vulnerability. The target vulnerability is located in claimRewards() and relates to an incorrect interface call to IVoter.poolVote.

notes: The model completely missed the target vulnerability in the claimRewards function regarding the incorrect usage of the poolVote mapping as a function. Instead, it focused on a minor initialization issue in the withdraw function.
